# CLI Contract Rules

- Keep response shapes in `src/types/` stable for `projects`, `sessions`, and `messages`.
- Preserve source behavior:
  - `--source` accepts only `claude`, `codex`, or `cursor`. Omitting `--source` means all sources unless `MMR_DEFAULT_SOURCE` supplies a default.
  - `--source all` is not a valid value.
  - The read/query commands (`projects`, `sessions`, `messages`, `export`, `remember`) work without `--source`.
- `sessions` and `messages` accept optional `--project`, optional `--all`, and `messages` accepts optional `--session`.
  - When `--project` is given without `--source`, search all sources.
  - Without `--project` and without `--all`, auto-discover the cwd project by default.
  - If cwd auto-discovery fails, fall back to all items across all projects/sources.
  - If cwd auto-discovery succeeds but there are no matching records, return the empty result instead of falling back.
  - `messages --session <id>` without `--project` bypasses cwd auto-discovery and searches all projects instead; if `--source` is omitted, print the narrowing hint on stderr.
- `export` accepts optional `--project`.
- `export` with no `--project` infers project from cwd: Codex = canonical path, Claude/Cursor = path with `/` -> `-` and a leading hyphen. Output is `ApiMessagesResponse` (same as `messages`). `--source` applies to export the same way and determines which source queries are merged.
- `remember` sends session transcripts to the backend chosen by `--agent` (`gemini`, `codex`, or `cursor`). When `--agent` is omitted, `MMR_DEFAULT_REMEMBER_AGENT` applies if set; otherwise the default is `cursor` (`composer-2-fast` unless `--model` is set).
  - Base system instruction: agent identity + input format only. It must not contain output-directing language.
  - Output instruction: without `--instructions`, use the default Purpose/Output Format/Rules/Resume Instructions block. With `--instructions`, replace that entire block with the user's text.
  - The user prompt stays neutral (`Analyze the following AI coding session transcript(s).`) so the system instruction controls output behavior.
  - `remember` defaults to markdown stdout; use `-O json` to return `RememberResponse` JSON.
- Keep `messages` pagination semantics: page from the newest matching window, then return that page in chronological order.
- Each `ApiSession` and `ApiMessage` includes per-item `source` and `project_name` metadata.
- Keep stdout uncolored; only human-facing stderr diagnostics may use color.

## Example

```rust
// GOOD
let descending = chronological.into_iter().rev().collect::<Vec<_>>();
let mut paged = apply_pagination(descending, limit, offset);
paged.reverse();

// BAD: breaks chronological return contract
let paged = apply_pagination(chronological, limit, offset);
```
